AI Code Review Iteration1 Reliability: Functionality SeverityHigh Querying with a random partition key generated by `Guid.NewGuid().ToString()` will not validate the health of the Cosmos DB store effectively. Cosmos DB will return an empty result set for a non-existent partition key without actually testing the ability to read data or the health of the collection. It might be better to use a known partition key or perform a query that actually retrieves data to validate the store's health. Here is the suggested code: ```suggestion string knownPartKey = "knownPartitionKey"; // Use a known partition key for health check var documents = await docContainer.QueryDocumentsAsync(knownPartKey, q => q.Take(1)); if (!documents.Any()) { throw new Exception("No documents found in the specified partition key, indicating potential health issues."); } ``` This comment refers to line 40 to 41 in the new file.
